itemLabel: Jane Harley, Countess of Oxford and Countess Mortimer

wikipedia_page.main: Jane Elizabeth Harley, Countess of Oxford and Countess Mortimer (née Scott; 1774–1824) was an English noblewoman, known as a patron of the Reform movement and a lover of Lord Byron.
